articles.description: David Nichols scored 25 points, 19 in the second half, leading five into double figures and Albany defeated UMass Lowell 91-81 Thursday night, notching its fourth straight 20-win season.
articles.headline: Nichols leads Albany past UMass Lowell 91-81

articles.description: Isaiah Washington's layup with seven seconds remaining lifted Quinnipiac to a 71-70 victory over Manhattan on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Washington's bucket wins it for Quinnipiac 71-70

articles.description: Josh Reaves feeds Mike Watkins, who gets behind the defense for an alley-oop dunk.
articles.headline: Watkins slips backdoor for alley-oop

images.caption: Josh Reaves feeds Mike Watkins, who gets behind the defense for an alley-oop dunk.
images.name: Watkins slips backdoor for alley-oop

articles.description: Rasheem Dunn scored 24 and hit a go-ahead layup late and St. Francis (Brooklyn) sank 5 of 6 free throws in the final 33 seconds to hold off LIU Brooklyn 84-79 on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Dunn rallies St Francis to 84-79 win over LIU Brooklyn

articles.description: Jason Dunne scored 19 points with four 3-pointers and nine rebounds, J.R. Lynch scored 13 points and made four free throws in the final 16 seconds, and Hartford beat Maine 67-63 on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Lynch's free throws help Hartford down Maine 67-63

articles.description: James Scott and Nick Masterson each scored 27 points, Anthony Wilson calmly sank two free throws on his first trip to the line with 1.1 seconds on the clock and Kennesaw State defeated Florida Gulf Coast 97-93 Thursday night, ending the Eagles'...
articles.headline: Kennesaw State beats FGCU 97-93, ending 13-game win streak

videos.description: Quentin Goodin does it himself as he blows by Wisconsin defeners for the lay-in.
videos.headline: Goodin cuts to the hoop with speed for Xavier

videos.description: Wisconsin's Khalil Iverson makes use of a great pass from Ethan Happ on this big two-handed jam.
videos.headline: Iverson goes way up for big dunk

videos.description: Xavier's J.P. Macura uses subtle look to the lane and gives himself enough space to get under the hoop for two.
videos.headline: Macura makes basket with misdirection

videos.description: Wisconsin's Brad Davidson makes use of the glass while showing off his range.
videos.headline: Davidson banks in the 3-pointer

videos.description: Brad Davidson takes it down the court after the turnover and knocks down the turn-around jumper for the Badgers.
videos.headline: Davidson steal leads to turn-around jumper

videos.description: Khalil Iverson gets a big block for Wisconsin, but Xavier gets the rebound and Trevon Bluiett knocks down the 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Blueitt hits 3 for Xavier

videos.description: Khalil Iverson gets left open under the hoop as he throws down a big dunk assisted by Ethan Happ for the Badgers.
videos.headline: Iverson gets open for easy jam

videos.description: Aleem Ford ties the game at 64-64 with this open 3-pointer for Wisconsin.
videos.headline: Ford ties it up with 3-pointer for Badgers

videos.description: D'Mitrik Trice hits a long two-pointer to put the Badgers up 66-64 late in the second half.
videos.headline: Trice gives Badgers lead with jumper

videos.description: Xavier takes advantage on the fastbreak with a one-handed alley-oop from J.P. Macura.
videos.headline: Macura throws down one-handed oop

videos.description: Xavier has a big second half to top the home team Wisconsin 80-70.
videos.headline: Xavier gets revenge on Wisconsin
